            "answer_text": "Put your iPod in Diagnostic Mode: Hold down the select button and the top menu button at the same time.Wait for the iPod to restart and then switch from the menu button to the left rewind button.It will reboot in diagnostic mode.Select MENU for Manual Test, then select IO > HardDrive > HDSMARTDataYou\u2019ll see something like this: Retracts: 889 Reallocs: 12 Pending Sectors: 0 PowerOn Hours: 2202 Start/Stops: 894 Temp: Current 24c Temp: Min 10c Temp: Max 50c If your pending sectors are anything but 0, you probably have a bad hard drive. ",
